As the premier marketplace and original platform where this all started, @nike and @ebaysneakers have come together to celebrate 20 years of Nike SB and commemorate Sandy Bodecker and the @bodeckerfound . So from today until December 14 eBay will be auctioning off 10 collectors edition boxes which will include a pair of “Tribute Dunks”, the new  Nike SB eBay dunk and a collectible saw, all packaged in a first-of-its-kind skateable shoe box. All proceeds will support The Bodecker Foundation. 

Smash that link in bio if you want a piece of skateboarding history!

Thanks to all who showed to “Skate Em Out” this weekend! If you copped, congrats. If you didn’t, that’s part of the game. Being a sneakerhead is all about the hunt. Failure makes you stronger. Don’t give up, because the game is fun. 

Thank you @ebay @ebaysneakers @nikesb and @bodeckerfound for hosting such a great event bringing friends together for an awesome weekend!!! Big love ❤️

While Nike celebrated a half century, Nike SB was throwing their own 20-year party. Let’s rewind to 2002 to where it all began, for a second time.

After many unsuccessful forays into skateboarding, Nike tapped a visionary by the name of Sandy Bodecker to lead a new charge. Fresh off his success integrating Nike into an equally challenging world of global football, Sandy quickly had Nike heading in the right direction with skateboarding, too.

Tap the 🔗 in our bio to see how Nike Skateboarding navigated the last two decades and get a glimpse of where they’re going.
